, from deserts to Antarctica to outer space. Hurley also introduces some of the innovators who have advanced the knowledge of lichens, from the ancient Greek philosopher Theophrastus to today’s professional lichenologists.With charming drawings by Susan Adele Edwards, Lichenpedia promises to put you in touch with the natural world in a new way by opening your eyes to these vital organisms, which are all around us, hidden in plain sight.Features a cloth cover with an elaborate foil-stamped design  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aLichens. 7aNATURE / Plants / General.2bisacsh  aAcid.  aAir.  aAlgae.  aAnimals.  aApothecia.  aBacteria.  aBark.  aBeard.  aBodies.  aBranches.  aCamouflage.  aCentury.  aColor.  aCompounds.  aCortex.  aCrustose lichens.  aCrustose.  aCyanobacteria.  aDye.  aEat.  aField.  aFoliose.  aFood.  aFruticose.  aFungal.  aFungi.  aFungus.  aGenus.  aGray.  aGrc.  aGrows.  aGrowth.  aHabitat.  aHair.  aHistory.  aHumans.  aIdentification.  aLand.  aLatin.  aLichen moth.  aLichen species.  aLichen.  aLichenologists.  aLower.  aMoss.  aMoth.  aNames.  aNature.  aNest.  aNitrogen.  aOrange.  aPlants.  aPurple.  aRocks.  aRole.  aSkin.  aSpecies.  aSpores.  aSubstances.  aSubstrate.  aSunburst.  aSurface.  aSymbiosis.  aThallus.  aTiny.  aTree hair.  aTree.  aTripe.  aUsnea.  aWater.1 aEdwards, Susan Adele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074975540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691239897?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691239897423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691239897/o